---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
import GreenBlock from '../components/GreenBlock.astro';
---
<Base title="About" current="About" description="The why behind MPower. People are already capable - they just need the right tools, in the right place, in their own language.">

  <section class="section">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="mono kicker">§ About · The why · 2026</div>
      <h1 class="display about-h1">
        People are <span class="i-accent">already capable.</span>
      </h1>
      <p class="body-lg about-lede">
        They just need the right tools, in the right place, in their own language. The world doesn't lack for expertise. It lacks for delivery.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <div class="container two-col">
      <div>
        <span class="mono accent">§ 01 · The name encodes the journey</span>
        <h2 class="heading two-col-title">Equip you. Then empower you.</h2>
      </div>
      <div>
        <p class="body-lg">
          MPowered is what people become, not something we do <em>to</em> you. The italic <span class="i-accent">2</span> in our tagline - Equip<span class="i-accent">2</span>MPower - is the bridge between knowing and doing.
        </p>
        <p class="body" style="margin-top: 24px; opacity: .82;">
          It is the stylised hinge in <em>Equip2MPower</em> - a real italic 2 at display sizes, a standard 2 in body text. A small, deliberate mark of the brand's confidence.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section-tight">
    <div class="container">
      <figure class="media">
        <div class="media-frame"><img src="/images/about.jpg" alt="Real people, real moments - Aotearoa." loading="lazy" /></div>
        <figcaption class="mono">§ Hands, not headshots · Aotearoa</figcaption>
      </figure>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <div class="container">
      <span class="mono accent">§ 02 · Three audiences</span>
      <h2 class="display audience-title">
        We start with the person <span class="i-accent">carrying the load.</span>
      </h2>
      <div class="audiences">
        <article>
          <h3 class="heading">Individuals</h3>
          <p class="body-lg">The one quietly figuring it out as they go - the owner running the business side of the farm, the principal leading the school, the leader without a playbook. Capable, and made to feel like the only one who doesn't know.</p>
        </article>
        <article>
          <h3 class="heading">Teams</h3>
          <p class="body-lg">Workplaces who want to grow their people together, built around their own context. Ongoing, not a one-workshop wonder.</p>
        </article>
        <article>
          <h3 class="heading">Communities</h3>
          <p class="body-lg">Networks of practice across a sector or a region, where knowledge moves sideways between peers, not just down from expert to learner.</p>
        </article>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <div class="container two-col">
      <div>
        <span class="mono accent">§ 03 · The compass</span>
        <h2 class="heading two-col-title">A vision for what equipped looks like.</h2>
      </div>
      <div>
        <p class="body-lg">
          A world where every capable person is also <span class="i-accent">equipped</span>, in their own language, in the moment they actually need it. Where knowledge moves sideways, not just down. Where leadership isn't reserved for the people with the title.
        </p>
        <p class="body" style="margin-top: 24px; opacity: .82;">
          The values that hold this up come from Radical HR, the practice behind MPower. Five of them. <a href="/values" class="vlink">Read them here</a>.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <GreenBlock kicker="§ Closer">
    <h2>You were always capable. <em>Now you're equipped.</em></h2>
  </GreenBlock>

</Base>

<style>
  .kicker { color: var(--c-spring); margin-bottom: 36px; }
  .about-h1 { font-size: var(--t-h1); max-width: 18ch; }
  .about-lede { margin-top: 32px; max-width: 64ch; opacity: .9; }

  .media { margin: 0; }
  .media-frame { border-radius: 4px; overflow: hidden; border: 1px solid var(--c-rule-soft); }
  .media-frame img { display: block; width: 100%; height: auto; aspect-ratio: 16 / 9; object-fit: cover; filter: saturate(.92) brightness(.97); }
  .media figcaption { font-family: var(--f-mono); font-size: var(--t-mono); letter-spacing: .1em; text-transform: uppercase; color: var(--c-fog); padding-top: 12px; }

  .two-col {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 1fr 2fr;
    gap: 64px;
  }
  .two-col-title { font-size: var(--t-h4); margin-top: 14px; max-width: 18ch; }

  .audience-title { font-size: var(--t-h2); margin-top: 28px; max-width: 22ch; }
  .audiences { margin-top: 56px; display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: 36px; }
  .audiences article {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 1fr 2fr;
    gap: 64px;
    padding-bottom: 36px;
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--c-rule);
  }
  .audiences h3 { font-size: var(--t-h3); }
  .audiences p { max-width: 56ch; opacity: .86; }
  .vlink { color: var(--c-spring); text-decoration: underline; text-underline-offset: 4px; }

  @media (max-width: 860px) {
    .two-col { grid-template-columns: 1fr; gap: 24px; }
    .audiences article { grid-template-columns: 1fr; gap: 16px; }
  }
</style>
